The paper deals with the problem of powering cellular networks using renewable energy sources, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI). The paper also presents a novel energy field model and analyzes its impact on network coverage, which falls under the category of game theory (GT), information theory (IT), and systems and control (SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a scheme for counteracting energy randomness, which involves power aggregation and redistribution, and thus can be related to power systems (PF).
